    <status>
    Since 2009, I have worked as scientific coordinator and then R&D Manager at Europeana, a unified access platform to digitized European Cultural Heritage, while keeping a research activity at the VU User Centric Data Science group. 
    At Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam, I have been involved in the STITCH, TELplus and Europeana Connect projects. I did my PhD studies at the French National Institute for Audiovisual and Universit√© Paris Sorbonne. My main research areas have been:
    - Application of Semantic Web/Linked Data technology in the Cultural Heritage domain: 
      - representation of metadata and controlled vocabularies, especially using SKOS
      - use of ontological mappings to access heterogeneous collections...
    - Semantic Web Languages and Technologies: Description Logic-based languages, ontology mapping algorithms. I have co-organized the library thesaurus mapping task in the OAEI evaluation campaign.
    - Ontology Foundations: Ontology Design Patterns, Formal and Core Ontologies.
    </status>

